## 3. Core Workflows & UML Sequence Diagrams

### SOS Trigger and Notification Sequence
The most critical workflow in Aegis is the activation of the SOS system. The client gathers GPS coordinates, contacts the Express API, writes the incident log, and alerts the emergency network simultaneously before recording ambient evidence.

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
  autonumber
  actor User as User in Danger
  participant App as React Dashboard
  participant GPS as Geolocation API
  participant Server as Express Server
  participant DB as MongoDB
  participant Notify as Notifier Service
  participant Gateway as Twilio & SMTP

  User->>App: Clicks "SOS" Button
  activate App
  App->>GPS: Request Current Coordinates
  alt GPS Available
    GPS-->>App: Latitude & Longitude Coordinates
  else GPS Fails / Timeout
    App->>App: Query Fallback IP Geolocation Service
  end
  App->>Server: POST /api/incidents/sos {lat, lng} (With JWT Token)
  activate Server
  Server->>Server: Verify JWT Token (protect Middleware)
  Server->>DB: Create Incident Log (status: 'active')
  activate DB
  DB-->>Server: Incident Created (_id, timestamps)
  deactivate DB

  Server->>DB: Find contacts where user == user.id
  activate DB
  DB-->>Server: Contacts List [name, phone, email]
  deactivate DB

  Server->>Notify: sendSOSTriggerAlerts(user, location, contacts)
  activate Notify
  
  par Send SMS
    Notify->>Gateway: Trigger Twilio SMS to Contacts
  and Send Email
    Notify->>Gateway: Trigger Nodemailer SMTP to Contacts
  end
  
  Notify-->>Server: Dispatch Initiated
  deactivate Notify
  
  Server-->>App: 201 Created & SOS Confirmation
  deactivate Server

  App->>App: Change Dashboard state to "Emergency Active"
  App->>App: Start MediaRecorder API (Record local audio evidence)
  
  Note over App: Recording continues for 10 seconds...
  
  App->>App: Stop MediaRecorder -> Create Audio Blob
  App->>Server: POST /api/incidents/:id/evidence (FormData multipart)
  activate Server
  Server->>Server: Save WebM file to backend/uploads
  Server->>DB: Add evidence metadata link to Incident Document
  DB-->>Server: Updated Document
  Server-->>App: 200 Evidence Upload Success
  deactivate Server
  deactivate App
```

