## 4. Live Location History & Resolution Flow

During an active SOS emergency, the client page periodically streams coordinate checkpoints to ensure rescuers can track movement. The session is closed when the user marks the emergency as resolved.

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
  autonumber
  participant App as React App (Dashboard)
  participant Server as Express Server
  participant DB as MongoDB

  loop Periodic Sync (While SOS is Active)
    App->>App: Fetch Current GPS Location
    App->>Server: PUT /api/incidents/:id/location {lat, lng}
    activate Server
    Server->>DB: Push coordinates to Incident.locationHistory & update Incident.location
    DB-->>Server: Updated Incident
    Server-->>App: 200 Success Response
    deactivate Server
  end

  User->>App: Clicks "Stop / Resolve SOS"
  activate App
  App->>Server: PUT /api/incidents/:id/resolve
  activate Server
  Server->>DB: Set Incident.status = 'resolved' & record Incident.resolvedAt
  DB-->>Server: Updated Incident
  Server-->>App: 200 Resolution Response
  deactivate Server
  App->>App: Reset State to "System Active" (Safe Mode)
  deactivate App
```

