## 5. API Endpoint Architecture

All endpoints (except login/registration and safety map data) are secured using JWT validation inside `authMiddleware.js`.

| Module | Method | Endpoint | Auth | Request Payload | Description |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **Auth** | `POST` | `/api/auth/register` | Public | `{name, email, password, phone}` | Registers a new account, hashes password, returns JWT. |
| **Auth** | `POST` | `/api/auth/login` | Public | `{email, password}` | Verifies credentials, generates JWT. |
| **Auth** | `GET` | `/api/auth/profile` | Private | *None* | Retrieves profile details for current logged-in user. |
| **Contacts** | `GET` | `/api/contacts` | Private | *None* | Fetches the list of trusted emergency contacts for the user. |
| **Contacts** | `POST` | `/api/contacts` | Private | `{name, phone, email, relationship}` | Registers a new emergency contact. |
| **Contacts** | `PUT` | `/api/contacts/:id` | Private | `{name, phone, email, relationship}` | Updates details of a specific emergency contact. |
| **Contacts** | `DELETE`| `/api/contacts/:id` | Private | *None* | Removes a contact from the user's list. |
| **Incidents**| `POST` | `/api/incidents/sos` | Private | `{latitude, longitude, address}` | Triggers SOS alert, writes incident, launches SMS/Email alerts. |
| **Incidents**| `PUT` | `/api/incidents/:id/location` | Private | `{latitude, longitude}` | Appends coordinate history to trace live route progression. |
| **Incidents**| `POST` | `/api/incidents/:id/evidence`| Private | `multipart/form-data` (file: `evidence`) | Receives audio/video recording files, stores locally. |
| **Incidents**| `PUT` | `/api/incidents/:id/resolve` | Private | *None* | Sets incident status to resolved and saves completion timestamp. |
| **Incidents**| `POST` | `/api/incidents/check-safety` | Private | `{latitude, longitude, radiusKm}` | Evaluates local risk index based on historical incident density. |
| **Incidents**| `GET` | `/api/incidents/danger-zones` | Public | *None* | Lists coordinates of all historical incidents for map overlays. |
| **Incidents**| `GET` | `/api/incidents/history` | Private | *None* | Fetches the past SOS activations triggered by the current user. |

